message: Suicide rates in Finland are half what they were in the 1990s and have reduced across all age groups – a shift which has been linked to a nationwide suicide prevention campaign when things were at their worst, alongside improved treatment for depression. But they remain well above the European average. One third of all deaths among 15- to 24-year-olds are caused by suicide.
